James de Villiers, News24 School building. (News24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Two men were held hostage at Solomon Qatyana Primary School, Lwandle, on Tuesday morning, police confirmed.It is believed that one of the men is the principal of the school.&nbsp;Police spokesperson Andr&egrave; Traut said the men had since&nbsp;been released and sustained no injuries.&nbsp;A case of kidnapping has been opened, Traut said.&nbsp;No arrests have been made and no further information on the circumstances surrounding the incident was available.&nbsp;Western Cape Education Department&nbsp;spokesperson Paddy Atwell did not respond to a request for comment.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.